"title": "5149: eyes",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5149: eyes",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The part of the body designed for seeing.  In Scripture eyes are often associated with light, watchfulness or spiritual understanding, whereas blindness may be a metaphor for darkness, ignorance of God or rebellion against him.  The eyes of God watch over all his creation.</p>\n<h2>Eyes are part of the physical body</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:65\">DEU 28:65</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job11:20\">JOB 11:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job31:16\">JOB 31:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:3\">PSA 69:3</a></p>\n<h3>Eyes may represent the whole person</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:23\">LUK 10:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:7\">REV 1:7</a></p>\n<h3>Eyesight is a vital sense</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:22\">MAT 6:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps54:7\">PSA 54:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:12\">PRO 20:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam4:17\">LAM 4:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:5\">MAT 11:5</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:22\">LUK 7:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:33\">MAT 20:33</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:51\">MRK 10:51</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:41\">LUK 18:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:27\">ACT 28:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:17\">1CO 12:17</a></p>\n<h3>Eyes may have a powerful emotional effect</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:9\">SNG 4:9</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Eyes reflect character, feelings and emotions</h3>\n<p>Malice:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:19\">PSA 35:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:13\">PRO 6:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov10:10\">PRO 10:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:30\">PRO 16:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps101:5\">PSA 101:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:4\">PRO 21:4</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:5\">MRK 3:5</a> <em>anger</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:21\">MRK 10:21</a> <em>love</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps88:9\">PSA 88:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:33-John11:35\">JHN 11:33–11:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:14\">2PE 2:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:16\">1JN 2:16</a></p>\n<h2>God's eyes are upon all his creation</h2>\n<h3>God is aware of everything</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job34:21\">JOB 34:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:7\">1SA 16:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps94:9\">PSA 94:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:16\">PSA 139:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov15:3\">PRO 15:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos9:8\">AMO 9:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab1:13\">HAB 1:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech3:9\">ZEC 3:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech4:10\">ZEC 4:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:13\">HEB 4:13</a></p>\n<h3>God watches over his people with care</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:15\">PSA 34:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut11:12\">DEU 11:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:29\">1KI 8:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs9:3\">1KI 9:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps1:6\">PSA 1:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps121:3-Ps121:5\">PSA 121:3–121:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov22:12\">PRO 22:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:12\">1PE 3:12</a></p>\n<h3>God's eyes symbolise his assessment of human behaviour</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:8\">GEN 6:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:26\">EXO 15:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg2:11\">JDG 2:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs15:5\">1KI 15:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor8:21\">2CO 8:21</a></p>\n<h2>Human eyes may symbolise spiritual vision</h2>\n<h3>God opens eyes in a spiritual sense</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:18\">PSA 119:18</a></strong> <em>The “opening of eyes” is an important biblical metaphor for revelation</em>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:18\">EPH 1:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num24:3-Num24:4\">NUM 24:3–24:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs6:17\">2KI 6:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra9:8\">EZR 9:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa35:5\">ISA 35:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:1\">ISA 61:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:22-Matt6:23\">MAT 6:22–6:23</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:34-Luke11:36\">LUK 11:34–11:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:18\">ACT 26:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:27\">HEB 11:27</a></p>\n<h3>Human eyes should be directed towards God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:5\">PSA 34:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps123:1-Ps123:2\">PSA 123:1–123:2</a></strong> <em>Lifting one's eyes towards God is an important biblical image of prayer.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:12\">2CH 20:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps25:15\">PSA 25:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps27:4\">PSA 27:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:26\">ISA 40:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:1\">JHN 17:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:55\">ACT 7:55</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:16\">2CO 3:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:2\">HEB 12:2</a></p>\n<h2>Human eyes will ultimately see God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job19:25-Job19:27\">JOB 19:25–19:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa33:17\">ISA 33:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:24\">JHN 17:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor13:12\">1CO 13:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:2\">1JN 3:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:4\">REV 22:4</a></p>\n<h2>Eyes are a channel of temptation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:8-Matt4:9\">MAT 4:8–4:9</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:5-Luke4:7\">LUK 4:5–4:7</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:6\">GEN 3:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:39\">NUM 15:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:21\">JOS 7:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam11:2\">2SA 11:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:37\">PSA 119:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl2:10\">ECC 2:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl6:9\">ECC 6:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:28-Matt5:29\">MAT 5:28–5:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:16\">1JN 2:16</a></p>\n<h3>Eyes should be guarded against evil</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job31:1\">JOB 31:1</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov4:25\">PRO 4:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps101:3\">PSA 101:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa33:15-Isa33:16\">ISA 33:15–33:16</a> <em>The direction of human eyes is a matter of choice.</em></p>\n<h2>Closing one's eyes may symbolise indifference to God and his will</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:15\">MAT 13:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:10\">ISA 6:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov28:27\">PRO 28:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek22:26\">EZK 22:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:16-Matt23:17\">MAT 23:16–23:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:41\">JHN 9:41</a></p>",
